<taxonomicName box="[479,652,1896,1920]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Stenotortor" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="361" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subhimalaya">
<emphasis box="[479,652,1896,1920]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="361">S. subhimalaya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with following differences: crown with two oblique short stripes on either side of median line. Posterior margin of pronotum, dark and mesonoutm dark reddish brown; inner claval marginal band in 
<typeStatus box="[353,451,1968,1993]" pageId="5" pageNumber="361">holotype</typeStatus>
complete but in 
<typeStatus box="[648,745,1969,1993]" pageId="5" pageNumber="361">paratype</typeStatus>
